<p>31-03: I noticed the grains in 100% soy donâ€™t reproduce and their effectiveness starts to decline. The grains in 100% milk have a steady consistency, but the mix-grains ferment crazy fast. Yeast and bacteria work more effective when submitted to manageable amounts of stress, but i also hope they react well to the glucose added. The soy-kefir has a very strong soy taste which is displeasing. Hopefully i can successfully make oatmilk-kefir in the future, which probably doesnâ€™t have a strong by-taste.</p>

<p>I switched to store bought soy milk since it wasnâ€™t doable to make soy-milk each morning, and the grains seem to react better on the store bought milk, probably due the higher sugar content.</p>

<p>07-04: The soy/milk grains are now completely converted to soymilk. Of all the batches, theyâ€™ve reproduces the most, going from 20g to 42g (where the milkgrains reached 35g and te soygrains shrunk to 17g). I hope the grains stay vital and donâ€™t need lactose anymore. Further tests will get their own page ;)</p>

